/*!

\page trademgen-config
	Configuration Script for the C++ Simulated Travel Demand Generation Library

\section sec_synopsis SYNOPSIS
<b>trademgen-config</b> <tt>[--prefix] [--version] [--libs] [--cflags]</tt>

\section sec_description DESCRIPTION

\e trademgen-config is a tool that is used by configure to determine the
compiler and linker flags that should be used to compile and link
programs that use \e TraDemGen. It is also used internally by the .m4
macros, that are included with \e TraDemGen, for GNU autoconf.

\section sec_options OPTIONS

\e trademgen-config accepts the following options:

 \b --help<br>
    Display this help and exit

 \b --prefix<br>
    Show the TraDemGen installation prefix.

 \b --version<br>
    Print the currently installed version of TraDemGen on the standard output.

 \b --libs<br>
    Print the linker flags that are necessary to link with the TraDemGen library.

 \b --cflags<br>
    Print the compiler flags that are necessary to compile with the
    TraDemGen library.

 \b --sampledir<br>
    Show where the (StdAir CSV) sample files are located.

 \b --mandir<br>
    Show where the manual pages are located.

 \b --infodir<br>
    Show where the information pages are located.

 \b --docdir<br>
    Show the documentation base directory.

 \b --htmldocpath<br>
    Show where the HTML documentation is located.

 \b --refmanpath<br>
    Show where the PDF documentation is located.

\section sec_see_also SEE ALSO
 \b trademgen(1), \b boost-config(1), \b trademgen-library(3)

